version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-04-18"
abstract: >-
  A fully automated, explainable binary classification pipeline
  that distinguishes vascular from non-vascular cutaneous ulcers
  using clinical photographs. The architecture combines BiomedCLIP
  (a biomedical vision-language foundation model, ViT-B/16), UNI 
  (a computational pathology foundation model, ViT-L/16), and
  EfficientNet-B0 (CNN) through late fusion, with Macenko colour
  normalisation and dual explainability (GradCAM++ and attention
  rollout). Trained on 1,339 images with stratified 5-fold
  cross-validation, achieving AUC-ROC 0.951 (CV) and 0.941
  (held-out test set) with 0.852 sensitivity for vascular ulcers.
